source.name: Annual Production Figures of United States Currency
source.description: Provided by the Bureau of Engraving and Printing (BEP), a bureau of the U.S. Department of the Treasury, this dataset details the number of $1, $2, $5, $10, $20, $50, and $100 notes printed each year by the bureau.
